# Copy to `.env` locally (never commit `.env`). Use placeholders only in docs and commits.
#
# ── agent-vcr record / recordTrace ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# OpenAI-compatible HTTP API (OpenAI, Groq, Azure OpenAI proxy, local gateways, …).
# https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Optional: same key in JSON instead of env — see record.config.json `apiKey`.
# For Groq, set baseURL in config and put your Groq key in OPENAI_API_KEY or apiKey.
# For Ollama (http://localhost:11434/v1), a dummy value is often enough.

# ── OpenAI SDK adapter (`agent-vcr/adapters/openai`) ─────────────────────────
# `new OpenAI()` reads OPENAI_API_KEY by default (same variable as above).

# ── Anthropic SDK adapter (`agent-vcr/adapters/anthropic`) ────────────────────
# https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ── Vercel AI SDK (`agent-vcr/adapters/vercel-ai`) ────────────────────────────
# With @ai-sdk/openai: OPENAI_API_KEY (same as OpenAI).
# Other providers (e.g. @ai-sdk/google) use their own env names — see Vercel AI docs.

# ── LangChain.js (`agent-vcr/adapters/langchain` + ChatOpenAI) ────────────────
# Typically OPENAI_API_KEY; LangChain may also honor model-specific settings.
